        "title": "The Karigars",
        "content": "<p>For <strong>Dhiman Singhji</strong>, the work has never been about making more, but making it right. Years of practice have shaped a way of working where the hand leads, and the eye decides when a batch is ready. There is a quiet satisfaction in knowing that the method remains unchanged. In a time where most things are made by machines, he believes there are still a few who understand the value of craft done by hand. To him, it is not just preparation, but a responsibility to keep the original form of these recipes intact.</p>"
